## Review finding from certified-app-v2-5g6

## Problem
In `src/lib/auth/auth-context.tsx`, the `signOut` callback awaits `fetch('/api/auth/logout')` before clearing local state. If the fetch throws (network error, server down), the catch block sets an error message but does NOT clear `isAuthenticated`, `did`, or `pdsUrl`. The user appears stuck as signed-in and cannot sign out without a page refresh.

## Evidence
```typescript
const signOut = useCallback(async () => {
  try {
    setError(null);
    await fetch("/api/auth/logout", { method: "POST" });  // ← if this throws...
    setIsAuthenticated(false);  // ← ...these lines are never reached
    setDid(null);
    setPdsUrl(null);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Sign out error:", err);
    setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Failed to sign out");
    // ← state NOT cleared — user stuck signed in
  }
}, []);
```

## Fix
Move the state-clearing calls to a `finally` block, or clear state before the fetch (optimistic sign-out). The server-side session cleanup is best-effort; the client should always clear its local state.

```typescript
const signOut = useCallback(async () => {
  // Clear local state immediately (optimistic)
  setIsAuthenticated(false);
  setDid(null);
  setPdsUrl(null);
  try {
    await fetch("/api/auth/logout", { method: "POST" });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Sign out error (server-side cleanup failed):", err);
    // Local state already cleared — user is signed out client-side
  }
}, []);
```

